&lt;p&gt;Happened to me several times. Use data.table package. When you only have 1 column that you need to refer to. Use either&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;lang-r s-code-block&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;hljs language-r&quot;&gt;DT&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-punctuation&quot;&gt;[[&lt;/span&gt;x&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-punctuation&quot;&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-punctuation&quot;&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;or&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;lang-r s-code-block&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;hljs language-r&quot;&gt;DT&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-punctuation&quot;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-punctuation&quot;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;..x&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-punctuation&quot;&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When you have 2 or more columns to refer to, make sure to use:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;lang-r s-code-block&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;hljs language-r&quot;&gt;DT&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-punctuation&quot;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-punctuation&quot;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;..x&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-punctuation&quot;&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;That x can be strings in another data.frame.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;if you want to select column with specific name then just do&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;lang-r s-code-block&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;hljs language-r&quot;&gt;A &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-operator&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;-&lt;/span&gt; mtcars&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-punctuation&quot;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-punctuation&quot;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;which&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-punctuation&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;conames&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-punctuation&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;mtcars&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-punctuation&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-operator&quot;&gt;==&lt;/span&gt;cols&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-punctuation&quot;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-number&quot;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-punctuation&quot;&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-punctuation&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-punctuation&quot;&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-comment&quot;&gt;# and then&lt;/span&gt;
colnames&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-punctuation&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;mtcars&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-punctuation&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-punctuation&quot;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;A&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-punctuation&quot;&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-operator&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;cols&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-punctuation&quot;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-number&quot;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-punctuation&quot;&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;you can run it in loop as well
reverse way to add dynamic name eg if A is data frame and xyz is column to be named as x then I do like this&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;lang-r s-code-block&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;hljs language-r&quot;&gt;A&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-operator&quot;&gt;$&lt;/span&gt;tmp &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-operator&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;-&lt;/span&gt; xyz
colnames&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-punctuation&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;A&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-punctuation&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-punctuation&quot;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;colnames&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-punctuation&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;A&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-punctuation&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-operator&quot;&gt;==&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-string&quot;&gt;&quot;tmp&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-punctuation&quot;&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-operator&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;x
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;again this can also be added in loop&lt;/p&gt;

